    "number": 29644,
    "state": "closed",
    "locked": false,
    "title": "[Attention] Make `split_decodes_and_prefills(..., require_uniform=True)` support padding",
    "user": {
      "login": "LucasWilkinson",
      "id": 8854186,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjg4NTQxODY=",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8854186?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/LucasWilkinson",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/following{/other_user}",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/gists{/gist_id}",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/starred{/owner}{/repo}",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/events{/privacy}",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/LucasWilkinson/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "user_view_type": "public",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "body": "with https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/28579 we pad attention metadata before building; in the case of a uniform decode request we want to make sure that num_decodes matches the cudagraph size so that attention schedulers receive the same batch size as the graph was captured with. Currently we have work around this in all the existing attention backends (e.g. https://github.com/vllm-project/FlashMLA/pull/3) since we used to pad for attention after building attention metadata so this was always the case. But this is needed https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/27532 since the FlashMLA FP8 Sparse Kernels do not have this workaround yet.\n\nThe `| (query_lens == 0)` is removed from:\n\n```\n        is_prefill = (query_lens > decode_threshold) | (query_lens == 0)\n```\nas a small cleanup since this is not actually required (since this is actually not needed given we do actually want to treat them as decades in the case of full-decode batches and if there is a prefill it will come computed as the first prefill so these entries will be ignored anyways.\n\nTest Plan:\n\nCI",
    "created_at": "2025-11-28T04:50:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2025-12-09T07:24:02Z",
    "closed_at": "2025-12-09T07:24:02Z",
